  [33m> Write[0m(file_path='/Users/nomind/Code/Tengu/tengu-cockpit/benchmarks/double-agent-tdd/worktrees/duh-gpt54/docs/wiki/Double-Agent-TDD.md', content='# Double-Agent TDD\n\n## Overview\n\n`duh tdd` runs a strict red-green-refactor workflow with two cooperating subagents:\n\n- **Navigator** — drafts the test spec, proposes the refactor, and validates the final result.\n- **Driver** — writes the failing test, makes it pass with the minimum change, and applies the refactor.\n\nD.U.H. enforces the sequence in Python. The model does not decide whether to skip phases.\n\n## Phase order\n\nThe command always runs these phases in this order:\n\n1. Navigator drafts the test spec.\n2. Driver writes the failing test and D.U.H. runs the test command. RED must fail.\n3. Driver writes the minimum implementation and D.U.H. runs the same test command. GREEN must pass.\n4. Navigator proposes a behavior-preserving refactor.\n5. Driver applies that refactor.\n6. Navigator validates that tests still pass and the refactor landed cleanly.\n\nIf the RED phase unexpectedly passes, D.U.H. stops the flow and asks the Navigator to tighten the spec. The session ends with `red_not_failing` instead of advancing to GREEN.\n\n## Usage\n\n```bash\nduh tdd "add parsing for TOML config files" --test-command "pytest tests/unit/test_config.py -q"\n```\n\n### Flags\n\n- `--test-command` — required. The command D.U.H. runs after RED, GREEN, and final refactor validation.\n- `--driver-agent-type` — defaults to `coder`.\n- `--navigator-agent-type` — defaults to `reviewer`.\n- `--driver-model` — model tier or literal model for the Driver. Defaults to `inherit`.\n- `--navigator-model` — model tier or literal model for the Navigator. Defaults to `inherit`.\n- global flags like `--model`, `--provider`, and `--debug` still apply.\n\n## Worked example\n\n```bash\nduh \\\n  --provider anthropic \\\n  --model claude-sonnet-4-6 \\\n  tdd "fix username normalization in auth.py" \\\n  --test-command "pytest tests/unit/test_auth.py -q"\n```\n\nTypical flow:\n\n- Navigator writes a spec saying usernames should be normalized before lookup.\n- Driver adds a failing unit test for mixed-case usernames.\n- The test command fails with an assertion failure.\n- Driver makes the smallest production change to normalize before lookup.\n- The same test command passes.\n- Navigator suggests extracting the normalization step into a helper.\n- Driver applies the helper extraction.\n- Navigator confirms tests still pass and the helper refactor appears present.\n\n## Output\n\nThe command prints a concise phase transcript, including each phase name and test exit code where relevant. A successful run ends with:\n\n```text\nDouble-agent TDD: completed\n```\n\nCommon non-success states:\n\n- `red_not_failing`\n- `green_failed`\n- `validation_failed`\n- `navigator_*_error`\n- `driver_*_error`\n\n## Notes\n\n- The workflow reuses D.U.H.\'s existing subagent infrastructure (`duh.agents.run_agent`).\n- The orchestrator is sequential by design; this is not a `Swarm` parallel flow.\n- For deterministic tests of the CLI wrapper, you can pair it with the stub provider machinery already used elsewhere in D.U.H.\n')
